        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 2:30PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 229 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Oil City to near Mount
Pleasant. Movement was northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Oil City around 235 PM EDT.
Coleman around 240 PM EDT.
Edenville around 300 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Hope, North Bradley,
and Bombay.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
